<div class="govuk-width-container">
  <div class="govuk-main-wrapper">
    <div class="govuk-grid-row">
      <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
        <h1 class="govuk-heading-l">Get an adviser</h1>

        <p>Advisers provide free, one-to-one support by phone, text or email. They’re all experienced, former teachers.</p>
        
        <p>There are two types of advisers available depending on your circumstances.<p>
        
        <p>If you're in your final year of undergraduate study or already have a degree, you can get a teacher training adviser</p>
        
        <p>If you're an undergraduate student not in your final year of study, you can get an explore teaching adviser</p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Teacher training advisers</h2>
        
        <p>A teacher training adviser can help you get into teaching if you have a bachelor's degree class 2:2 (honours) or higher or are a final-year undergraduate student.</p>
        <p>Your adviser can help you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>get school experience</li>
          <li>understand available funding</li>
          <li>choose the right training</li>
          <li>write your personal statement</li>
          <li>prepare for interviews</li>
        </ul>
        
        <p>If you’re thinking about returning to teaching, you'll need to have qualified teacher status (QTS) and want to teach a secondary subject in England to get a teacher training adviser.</p>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Explore teaching advisers</h2>
        
        <p>An explore teaching adviser can help you find out what teaching is really like if you’re an undergraduate student not in your final year of study.</p>

        <p>Your adviser can help you:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>get school experience</li>
          <li>build confidence and transferable skills</li>
          <li>connect with other students who are considering teaching</li>
          <li>understand the process to become a teacher</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">Non-UK citizens</h2>
        
        <p>You can get a teacher training adviser if you have an overseas qualification equivalent to a bachelor’s degree with honours, class 2:2 or higher.</p>
        <p>Before you use this service as a non-UK citizen, you can check your qualifications by calling <%= link_to("0800 389 2500", "tel://08003892500") %>.</p>

        <a href="<%= teacher_training_adviser_step_path(:identity, params.to_unsafe_h.slice(:channel, :sub_channel)) %>" role="button" draggable="false" class="govuk-button govuk-!-margin-top-2 govuk-!-margin-bottom-8 govuk-button--start" data-module="govuk-button">
        Start now
        <svg class="govuk-button__start-icon" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="17.5" height="19" viewBox="0 0 33 40" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
          <path fill="currentColor" d="M0 0h13l20 20-20 20H0l20-20z" />
        </svg>
      </a>
        <p>Find teacher training options if you live in:</p>
        <ul class="govuk-list govuk-list--bullet">
          <li><a href="https://teachinscotland.scot">Scotland</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://educators.wales/">Wales</a></li>
          <li><a href="https://www.education-ni.gov.uk/articles/initial-teacher-education-courses-northern-ireland">Northern Ireland</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
